main event: A white, arc-shaped object was observed flashing on and off and disappearing instantly in Redwing, Wisconsin on 9th November 1952. The observation lasted for 20-30 minutes and it was reported by a civilian man.
interesting points: The object was observed flashing on and off and disappeared instantly, leading to the conclusion that it might have been a star due to its blinking characteristics and the long observation.
The report is from Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated unidentified flying objects (UFOs) in the 1950s.
The report mentions a preliminary interview conducted regarding the unidentified flying object sighting.
The sighting was observed for a significant duration of 20-30 minutes by a civilian man, adding credibility to the report.
The report indicates that the observation was made using naked eye visualization, suggesting that the object was visible without the aid of any special equipment.
sighted object: white, arc-shaped object flashing on and off
